basic structure for css section
<style>
</style>
everything goes within <style> brackets
color - h2 {color: red;}
classes - reusable style elements
.blue-text {
    color: blue;
  }
added thus h2 class="blue-text">CatPhotoApp</h2>
html class declarations don't start with a period, css classes do
class="your-class-here"
font size: font-size: 30px; as a property for css classes
font-size: 16px;
font-family: Monospace;
<img src="https://bit.ly/fcc-relaxing-cat">
.thin-red-border {
    border-color: red;
    border-width: 5px;
    border-style: solid;
<img class="class1 class2">
border-radius - rounds corners
border radius can be pixels or percent
<p>Here's a <a href="http://freecodecamp.com"> link to Free Code Camp</a> for you to follow.</p>
anchor tag <a> </a> links outside of page
# to replace anchor tag link until needed
<a href="#"><img src="https://bit.ly/fcc-running-cats"></a>
alt attribute - image description in text on hover-over
<img src="www.your-image-source.com/your-image.jpg" alt="your alt text">
unordered list:
<ul>
  <li>milk</li>
  <li>cheese</li>
</ul>
ordered list:
<ol>
  <li>Garfield</li>
  <li>Sylvester</li>
</ol>
input:
<input type="text">
placeholder for input:
<input type="text" placeholder="this is placeholder text">
submit data from a form:
<form action="/url-where-you-want-to-submit-form-data"></form>
submit button:
<button type="submit">this button submits the form</button>
make type in form required (e.g. text)
 <input type="text" required>
radio buttons:
<label><input type="radio" name="indoor-outdoor"> Indoor</label>
